CatDescriptText: Barbara Garnett, beautician's aide, 433 Burrows Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the hospital service rendered under Blue Cross plan is worth its present cost to the subscriber? Do you think the rates should be raised?  Why?"  answer reads: "Yes, I do think that the hospital service rendered under the Blue Cross plan is worth its present cost to the subscriber.  However, I do not know whether or not the proposed increase is justified because I don't know about the rates."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Barbara Garnett wearing light colored short sleeved shirt dress with belt, and long double strand chain link necklace, holding basket handbag and eyeglasses, standing in front of light colored stone block wall with granite wainscot, store window on right
